 {"id":"asupersync-00e","title":"[Foundation] Migration Path and Backward Compatibility Layer","description":"## Overview

This task implements a compatibility layer that allows gradual migration from traditional
message-based APIs to the new symbol-native paradigm. Users can adopt RaptorQ incrementally
while maintaining compatibility with existing code.

## Rationale

Production systems cannot switch protocols overnight. We need:
1. **Gradual adoption** - Enable RaptorQ on a per-operation basis
2. **API compatibility** - Existing code continues to work unchanged
3. **Performance parity** - Non-RaptorQ paths remain efficient
4. **Clear migration path** - Documentation and tooling for transition

## Technical Specification

### Compatibility Traits

```rust
/// Marker trait for types that can work with both paradigms
pub trait DualMode: Send + Sync {
    /// Whether this instance uses RaptorQ encoding
    fn uses_raptorq(&self) -> bool;

    /// Convert to symbol-native representation if not already
    fn to_symbol_native(self) -> Self;

    /// Convert to traditional representation if not already
    fn to_traditional(self) -> Self;
}

/// Extension trait for Result types in dual-mode context
pub trait ResultExt<T, E> {
    /// Convert result to symbol-native representation
    fn symbolize(self) -> Result<SymbolizedValue<T>, SymbolizedError<E>>;

    /// Convert result to traditional representation
    fn traditionalize(self) -> Result<T, E>;
}

/// Wrapper that can hold either traditional or symbol-native value
pub enum DualValue<T> {
    /// Traditional direct value
    Traditional(T),
    /// Symbol-encoded value with metadata
    SymbolNative {
        symbols: SymbolSet,
        object_id: ObjectId,
        _phantom: PhantomData<T>,
    },
}

impl<T: Serialize + DeserializeOwned> DualValue<T> {
    /// Get the underlying value, decoding if necessary
    pub fn get(&self) -> Result<T, DecodeError> {
        match self {
            Self::Traditional(v) => Ok(v.clone()),
            Self::SymbolNative { symbols, .. } => {
                decode_from_symbols(symbols)
            }
        }
    }

    /// Encode to symbols if not already symbol-native
    pub fn ensure_symbols(&mut self, config: &EncodingConfig) -> &SymbolSet {
        if let Self::Traditional(v) = self {
            let (symbols, object_id) = encode_to_symbols(v, config);
            *self = Self::SymbolNative {
                symbols,
                object_id,
                _phantom: PhantomData,
            };
        }
        match self {
            Self::SymbolNative { symbols, .. } => symbols,
            _ => unreachable\!(),
        }
    }
}
```

### Migration Mode Enum

```rust
/// Migration mode controls how operations handle dual-mode values
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Default)]
pub enum MigrationMode {
    /// Only use traditional mode (no RaptorQ)
    TraditionalOnly,
    /// Default to traditional, RaptorQ opt-in
    #[default]
    PreferTraditional,
    /// Use RaptorQ when beneficial, fall back to traditional
    Adaptive,
    /// Default to RaptorQ, traditional opt-in
    PreferSymbolNative,
    /// Only use RaptorQ (errors on traditional-only operations)
    SymbolNativeOnly,
}

impl MigrationMode {
    /// Whether to use RaptorQ for a given operation
    pub fn should_use_raptorq(&self, hint: Option<bool>, data_size: usize) -> bool {
        match (self, hint) {
            // Explicit hints always win
            (_, Some(true)) => true,
            (_, Some(false)) => false,
            // Mode-specific defaults
            (Self::TraditionalOnly, None) => false,
            (Self::SymbolNativeOnly, None) => true,
            (Self::PreferTraditional, None) => false,
            (Self::PreferSymbolNative, None) => true,
            // Adaptive mode uses heuristics
            (Self::Adaptive, None) => {
                // Use RaptorQ for larger payloads or distributed operations
                data_size > 1024 || is_distributed_context()
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Compatibility Combinators

```rust
/// Run a combinator with migration mode control
pub async fn with_migration_mode<F, Fut, T>(
    mode: MigrationMode,
    f: F,
) -> T
where
    F: FnOnce() -> Fut,
    Fut: Future<Output = T>,
{
    MIGRATION_MODE.scope(mode, f()).await
}

/// Combinator wrapper that supports both modes
pub struct DualJoin<T> {
    traditional: Option<Join<T>>,
    symbol_native: Option<SymbolJoin<T>>,
}

impl<T: Clone + Send + Sync> DualJoin<T> {
    pub fn new(mode: MigrationMode) -> Self {
        match mode {
            MigrationMode::TraditionalOnly |
            MigrationMode::PreferTraditional => Self {
                traditional: Some(Join::new()),
                symbol_native: None,
            },
            MigrationMode::SymbolNativeOnly |
            MigrationMode::PreferSymbolNative => Self {
                traditional: None,
                symbol_native: Some(SymbolJoin::new()),
            },
            MigrationMode::Adaptive => Self {
                traditional: Some(Join::new()),
                symbol_native: Some(SymbolJoin::new()),
            },
        }
    }

    /// Join futures, using appropriate implementation
    pub async fn join_all<I, F, Fut>(self, futures: I) -> Vec<Result<T, E>>
    where
        I: IntoIterator<Item = F>,
        F: FnOnce() -> Fut,
        Fut: Future<Output = Result<T, E>>,
    {
        if let Some(join) = self.symbol_native {
            // Symbol-native path with encoding/distribution
            join.join_all(futures).await
        } else if let Some(join) = self.traditional {
            // Traditional path
            join.join_all(futures).await
        } else {
            unreachable\!()
        }
    }
}
